      <h1 id="title">Satoru Iwata</h1>
      <h2> A Tribute to One of the Most Important People in Gaming History</h2>
      <div id="img-div">
        <img id="image" src="https://assets.reedpopcdn.com/nintendo-president-satoru-iwata-passes-away-at-55-1436761484412.jpg/BROK/resize/690%3E/format/jpg/quality/75/nintendo-president-satoru-iwata-passes-away-at-55-1436761484412.jpg" alt="Satoru Iwata">
        <figcaption id="img-caption"> Satoru Iwata, the beloved former President of Nintendo.</figcaption>
      </div>
      <p id="facts">Here are some general facts about the life of Satoru Iwata</p>
      <fieldset>
      <ul id="tribute-info">
          <li>Satoru Iwata was born December 6, 1959, in Hakkaido, Japan</li>
        <li>Satoru began developing his first game during high school</li>
        <li>Satoru became the President of Nintendo in 2002</li>
        <li>Satoru is recognized as the person who revitalized Nintendo and brought forth the Golden Years of the company</li>
        <li>Satoru helped develop some of the most popular gaming systems ever created, such as the Nintendo DS and the Nintendo Wii</li>
        <li>Satoru Iwata passed away on July 11, 2015, at the age of 55</li>
      </ul>
      </fieldset>
      <i>"On my business card, I am a corporate president. In my mind, I am a game developer. But in my heart, I am a gamer."</i>
      <i>-- Satoru Iwata</i>
      <p>If you have time, you should read more about Satoru Iwata and his incredible life and legacy on his <a id="tribute-link" target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Satoru_Iwata">Wikipedia entry</a>.</p>
